700566f-a.text:
Broadway (left), south from W. 238th Street, showing the elevated structure of the I.R.T. subway line thereon. On the right is Kingsbridge Avenue, running south from its commencement
point at W. 238th Street.
September 28, 1913
Gift of M. Vaxer

700567f-a.text:
Broadway (left), south from West 238th Street, showing the elevated structure of the I.R.T. Van Cortlandt Park subway line thereon. On the extreme right is Kingsbridge Ave., running south from its commencement point at West 238th Street.

1915.

James Suydam.

700364f.text:
West 238th Street, north side, east from Broadway to Review Place.  The 2-story building, at the corner bears No. 5820 Broadway.  On the extreme right, at the N.W. corner of Review Place, is shown under construction of a 5-story apartment house, bearing No. 233.  Also shown (left) under construction is a 5-story building bearing No. 5824 Broadway.  Overhead appears part of the 238th Street elevated station of the I.R.T. Van Cortlandt Park subway line.

About 1915.
James Suydam
Neg. No 77
